## 6. switch vs if-else — Quick Reference

| Feature | switch | if-else |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Works with | int, char, enum only | Any expression |
| Range checks | Not supported | Supported |
| Multiple conditions | Not supported | Supported (AND, OR) |
| Readability | Better for many exact values | Better for complex logic |
| Fall-through | Yes (controlled via break) | No |
| Default case | `default:` | Final `else` |

